Title: Exposure-response modeling of tocilizumab in rheumatoid arthritis using continuous composite measures and their individual components.
Name: Tocilizumab

Sentece: Two main groups of individual components were identified based on their different dynamics under tocilizumab treatment: (i) tender and swollen joint counts and patient and evaluator global assessment showed a slower decrease of their baseline value (half-life: 4.6 weeks, RSE: 24%) and the need for higher serum drug concentration (EC50 : 4.60 μg/mL, RSE: 103%, IIV: 359%) than (ii) C-reactive protein and erythrocyte sedimentation rate (half-life: 2.3 weeks, RSE 19%; EC50 : 0.878 μg/mL, RSE: 41%, IIV: 238%).
